What happened at #SaugusHighSchool is a tragedy, and all too relatable in communities across our state. In 2018, 104 Californians age 18 or younger were victims of firearm-related homicides, with 94 of them between the ages of 5 and 18.

Learn more: https://bit.ly/2CK2cpj

text: Babesia duncani though.
text_html: Babesia duncani though.

Seemay Chou, PhD | UCSF | Tick Talk: Advancing the Understanding and Prevention of Tick-borne Diseases. We are seeing more and more ticks each year. Marin's China Camp seems to have a relatively high rate of Borrelia infected ticks. #Marin @seemaychou @UCSF @CAPublicHealth

Seemay Chou, PhD | UCSF | Tick Talk: Advancing the Understanding and Prevention of Tick-borne Diseases. Paratransgenesis to control vectors - potential to add microbes to ticks that could block Borrelia from being transmitted. #ticks @seemaychou @UCSF @CAPublicHealth

Seemay Chou, PhD | UCSF | Tick Talk: Advancing the Understanding and Prevention of Tick-borne Diseases. Ticks carry multiple pathogens. Co-infections are serious problem for human diagnosis and treatment. #Coinfections #Babesia #ehrlichia @seemaychou @UCSF @CAPublicHealth

Seemay Chou, PhD | UCSF | Tick Talk: Advancing the Understanding and Prevention of Tick-borne Diseases. We need better diagnostics. Charles Chiu, MD, PhD of UCSF has been working on a Lyme disease diagnostic. @seemaychou @UCSF @CAPublicHealth

Seemay Chou, PhD | UCSF | Tick Talk: Advancing the Understanding and Prevention of Tick-borne Diseases Many people don't notice their tick bite and only half of Lyme patients may get a rash. There is a limited window of treatment. @seemaychou @UCSF @CAPublicHealth

Seemay Chou, PhD | UCSF | Tick Talk: Advancing the Understanding and Prevention of Tick-borne Diseases Borrelia doesn't hang out in blood. Borrelia makes a home in tissue but will come out and head towards a tick that is biting the host. @seemaychou @UCSF @CAPublicHealth

Seemay Chou, PhD | UCSF | Tick Talk: Advancing the Understanding and Prevention of Tick-borne Diseases. Borrelia have been found in Amblyomma ticks, but those ticks are not as efficient as Ixodes ticks at transmitting Borrelia to humans. @seemaychou @UCSF @CAPublicHealth

Did you know? Each year more than 250,000 Americans visit a hospital due to pneumonia. Legionnaires’ disease, a type of pneumonia, is caused by breathing in droplets of water containing related bacteria.  Learn how to lower your risks:
https://cdc.gov/legionella/downloads/fs-legionnaires.pdf …

text:
"Childhood Whooping Cough Vaccine Protects Most Children For At Least 5 years"
Sorry. Never has been life-long. 
Most of us who have had children vaccinated with the diptheria, tetanus and pertussis vaccine understand 'boosters' required every 10 years.
https://www.cdc.gov/media/matte/2011/10_whooping_cough.pdf …
